text.tspan: Labor force participation rates for women ages 15-24, 2020 vs 1980
Shown is the labor force participation rate for women in 2020 (horizontal axis) and in 1980 (vertical axis). The female labor force participation
rate corresponds to the proportion of the female population ages 15-24 that is economically active. All figures correspond to national
estimates, without ILO corrections (see limitations and exceptions in the sources).
Labor force participation rate for ages 15-24, female in 2020
Labor force participation rate for ages 15-24, female in 1980
Data source: International Labour Organization (via World Bank)
